370
00:37:07,330 --> 00:37:09,110
Don't even bring up those punks!

371
00:37:09,110 --> 00:37:15,010
If I think about what you went through because of those punks, I still have anger rising up inside me!

372
00:37:15,010 --> 00:37:17,800
They say you shouldn't twist the truth.

373
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:20,430
Why was that because of Brother and his mother?

374
00:37:20,430 --> 00:37:23,590
The situation somehow just played out that way.

375
00:37:23,590 --> 00:37:26,940
Also, you hold some responsibility for why Brother became that way.

376
00:37:26,940 --> 00:37:31,440
You know that yourself, which is why you're punishing yourself right now. Am I wrong?

377
00:37:34,300 --> 00:37:36,140
Stop being stubborn.

378
00:37:36,140 --> 00:37:40,370
What are you going to do if Mother finds another man?

379
00:37:40,370 --> 00:37:44,620
What? That woman is meeting another man?

380
00:37:46,210 --> 00:37:51,260
Wait... What? M-Mother?

381
00:37:52,590 --> 00:37:54,900
Gosh, I'm saying you should go see her before it's too late.

382
00:37:54,900 --> 00:38:00,210
There's not much to happiness. Happiness is when you live with the person you like and annoy them.

383
00:38:02,290 --> 00:38:04,550
And dress up.

384
00:38:04,550 --> 00:38:09,750
Take a shower, too! Put on some cologne, also!

385
00:38:09,750 --> 00:38:12,350
And try going to places like this.

386
00:38:14,700 --> 00:38:19,920
What's this? Black Tea and Madeleine?

387
00:38:19,920 --> 00:38:22,910
What? Is this a place you go taste testing?

388
00:38:27,730 --> 00:38:32,920
That punk. Always makes me mad after he does something nice for me.

389
00:38:32,920 --> 00:38:35,660
What smell is he talking about?

390
00:38:50,190 --> 00:38:53,590
I'm the new owner of the rooftop house, and I wondered when you were going to come and pick this up?

391
00:38:53,590 --> 00:38:56,080
This crappy bed.

392
00:38:57,310 --> 00:39:01,380
You know that nowadays you have to pay even if you want to throw it away, right?

393
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:06,160
Well, you being busy is your problem. If you don't take this away within three days–

394
00:39:07,280 --> 00:39:11,120
What the? He hung up?

395
00:39:11,120 --> 00:39:14,370
How can he have such crap manners?

396
00:39:16,690 --> 00:39:20,340
Oppa! Oppa!

397
00:39:23,100 --> 00:39:27,570
Oppa! Oppa!

398
00:39:30,230 --> 00:39:33,080
Why aren't you answering when someone is calling for you?

399
00:39:33,100 --> 00:39:36,270
- What is it now?
- Change out the bathroom's tiles.

400
00:39:36,270 --> 00:39:39,190
Even though it's a rooftop room, it's really bad.

401
00:39:39,190 --> 00:39:43,320
Are you going to pay the deposit fee? If you pay that, I'll change out the tiles for you.

402
00:39:43,320 --> 00:39:47,790
I don't have that much money. At least change the wallpaper then!

403
00:39:47,790 --> 00:39:50,220
I changed it to the best quality silk wallpaper already,

404
00:39:50,230 --> 00:39:53,340
why would I change that?

405
00:39:53,340 --> 00:39:55,310
It doesn't go with the color of my closet.

406
00:39:55,370 --> 00:39:58,560
Then change your wardrobe.

407
00:39:58,560 --> 00:40:03,510
- Then at least change the floors! I really can't back down on this one.
- What's wrong with the floors now?

408
00:40:03,510 --> 00:40:06,680
My feet stick onto it because it's not marble.

409
00:40:06,680 --> 00:40:11,060
Change it to marble. I have something in mind. It's made in Italy─

410
00:40:11,060 --> 00:40:13,590
- You should just leave.
- What?

411
00:40:13,590 --> 00:40:17,720
I rented out the room for cheap because I was proud of you for wanting to truly live by yourself. But what?

412
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:20,350
Silk wallpapers and marble floors?

413
00:40:20,350 --> 00:40:23,400
There are a ton of people who want to live there besides you.

414
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:26,820
I'll call the realtor right now and you just─

415
00:40:26,820 --> 00:40:31,600
Yes, Curator Song? Oh, is that so? I didn't know.

416
00:40:31,600 --> 00:40:34,950
Hey, I'm not done talking.

417
00:40:34,950 --> 00:40:41,360
The director? No, I didn't receive an email.

418
00:40:41,360 --> 00:40:46,360
Well, it's still in the middle of the night over there, so she may not have checked it yet.

419
00:40:56,170 --> 00:41:00,230
