577
00:52:17,590 --> 00:52:22,310
Are you happy that you got a special promotion after throwing my dad into prison? Are you on cloud nine?

578
00:52:22,310 --> 00:52:24,080
Seeing me getting kicked out of a house that was like a palace

579
00:52:24,080 --> 00:52:26,590
and moving into a rooftop place, you must feel so relieve—

580
00:52:26,590 --> 00:52:30,070
Okay, I got it! I got it! Just take this.

581
00:52:30,070 --> 00:52:31,390
Happy?

582
00:52:31,390 --> 00:52:34,600
Don't try to pawn off your crappy bed to me.

583
00:52:34,600 --> 00:52:36,520
Then, what do you want?

584
00:52:36,520 --> 00:52:38,230
Buy me food.

585
00:52:38,230 --> 00:52:40,180
Why should I?

586
00:52:40,180 --> 00:52:44,560
You are good with jajangmyeon, right? The Chinese place, right here, looked good.

587
00:52:44,560 --> 00:52:47,180
Why in the world do I need to buy you food?

588
00:52:47,180 --> 00:52:50,230
Shall I order kanpungi?

589
00:52:50,230 --> 00:52:51,460
Chili shrimp sounds good, too.

590
00:52:51,460 --> 00:52:53,180
Hey, I don't like kanpungi.

591
00:52:53,180 --> 00:52:56,550
The chili shrimp is... No! Why would I buy you a meal?

592
00:52:56,550 --> 00:52:59,560
Because I am hungry.

593
00:52:59,560 --> 00:53:01,750
Why are you telling me if you feel hungry?

594
00:53:01,750 --> 00:53:03,040
Tangsuyuk?

595
00:53:03,040 --> 00:53:07,210
